.TH CASTE 1 "February 1, 2026" "caste 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
caste \- print a single-word hardware class
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B caste
[\fB\-\-reason\fR]
[\fB\-\-hwfacts\fR]
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
[\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B caste
command prints a single-word hardware class inferred from the system:
Mini, User, Developer, Workstation, or Rig.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-reason
Include a short explanation after the class.
.TP
.B \-\-hwfacts
Print detected hardware facts before the class output.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show a brief usage message.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B caste
Print the class only.
.TP
.B caste \-\-reason
Print the class and a short explanation.
.TP
.B caste \-\-hwfacts
Print detected hardware facts, then the class.
.TP
.B caste \-\-hwfacts \-\-reason
Print detected hardware facts, then the class and short explanation.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR uname (1)
